author: COMSOL
description:
The present example demonstrates how to set up the classical external-flow problem of solving for the high-speed, compressible, turbulent flow over the ONERA M6 wing. The problem involves finding a steady-state solution of the flow field around the 3D, swept wing geometry, immersed in a transonic flow at a moderately high angle of attack, leading to the formation of weak shocks on the upper surface of the wing.

Disclaimer: This model uses data from the ONERA M6 wing as a reference. This model is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by ONERA.
